e%20to%20five%20in%20advertising%2C%20and%20then%20wrote%20freelance%20stories%20in%20the%20mornings%2C%20evenings%2C%20and%20on%20weekends.%20There%20was%20even%20a%20six%20month%20stretch%20where%20I%20had%20a%20breaking%20news%20reporter%20gig%20on%20top%20of%20my%20day%20job%2C%20working%20from%206%20to%20midnight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20burnt%20out%2C%20obviously.%20The%20bigger%20problem%20was%20that%20my%20end%20goal%20continually%20shape-shifted.%20First%2C%20I%20just%20wanted%20to%20get%20paid%20for%20writing.%20Then%20I%20needed%20to%20write%20for%20more%20well-respected%20publications.%20Then%20I%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhollywood-leaving-los-angeles-remote-work-tv-movies-money-streaming-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emove%20to%20Los%20Angeles%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20become%20a%20TV%20writer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20scratched%20up%20this%20neverending%20ladder%2C%20something%20else%20was%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind%3A%20trail%20running.%20During%20the%20early%20days%20of%20COVID%20I%20had%20read%20Chris%20McDougall's%20memoir%20%26quot%3BBorn%20To%20Run%26quot%3B%20and%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebecome%20fascinated%20with%20the%20stories%20of%20people%20who%20could%20run%20100%20miles%2C%20on%20trails%2C%20over%20mountains.%20These%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-running-industrial-complex-marathons-instagram-ads-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehardcore%20runners%3C%2Fa%3E%20seemed%20alive%20and%20free%2C%20like%20hyper-athletic%20hippies%20who%20had%20completely%20unsubscribed%20to%20the%20traditional%20career-oriented%20lifestyle.%20They%20showed%20me%20it%20was%20possible%20to%20have%20goals%20that%20were%20entirely%20within%20my%20control.%20I%20realized%20how%20much%20vaster%20my%20dreams%20for%20my%20life%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20running%20after%20work%20in%20Griffith%20Park%2C%20trying%20to%20get%20a%20bit%20further%20up%20the%20steep%203-mile%20trail%20to%20the%20Observatory%20without%20walking.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20couldn't%20even%20get%20up%20the%20road%20into%20the%20park%20without%20stopping%20to%20catch%20my%20breath.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20few%20months%2C%20my%20breathing%20steadied%20and%20my%20calves%20didn't%20burn%20as%20badly.%20I%20studied%20the%20greats%20of%20the%20sport%2C%20and%20listened%20to%20podcasts%20with%20training%20tips%2C%20like%20how%20to%20lean%20forward%20as%20you%20run%20uphill.%20Eventually%20I%20could%20make%20it%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20Observatory%20%E2%80%94%20where%20I'd%20stop%20and%20immediately%20bend%20over%2C%20catch%20my%20breath%2C%20look%20down%20at%20the%20city%2C%20and%20feel%20a%20rush%20of%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20signed%20up%20for%20a%2050k%20trail%20race%20(32%20miles)%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bentry%20level%26quot%3B%20ultra%20distance%2C%20which%20to%20me%20felt%20like%20an%20impossible%20feat%20that%20made%20me%20sick%20to%20think%20about.%20But%20as%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-ran-my-first-marathon-advice-mistakes-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etraining%20intensified%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20my%20weekends%20started%20to%20revolve%20around%20getting%20enough%20sleep%20before%20my%20long%20runs%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20I%20felt%20more%20engaged%20with%20trail%20running%20than%20I%20had%20ever%20felt%20trying%20to%20pitch%20my%20pilot%20to%20a%20disinterested%20literary%20manager%20over%20a%20Zoom%20call%20%E2%80%94%20because%20I%20didn't%20care%20what%20anyone%20else%20thought.%20After%20workdays%20dealing%20with%20demanding%20clients%20and%20aggressive%20timelines%2C%20running%20the%20foothills%20of%20Los%20Angeles%20felt%20like%20playing%20hooky.%20I%20was%20out%20of%20the%20reach%20of%20cell%20service%2C%20spotting%20rattlesnakes%2C%20and%20peeing%20behind%20bushes.%20I%20had%20awoken%20a%20more%20feral%2C%20more%20childlike%20version%20of%20myself%2C%20and%20I%20was%20hooked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20years%20later%20and%20I've%20completed%20trail%20races%20ranging%20from%208%20to%20100%20miles.%20I%20use%20most%20of%20my%20PTO%20to%20go%20on%20running%20vacations%20or%20attend%20races.%20I%20traded%20my%20apartment%20in%20Echo%20Park%20for%20a%20cabin%20in%20the%20foothills%20of%20Angeles%20National%20Forest.%20I've%20abused%20my%20toe%20nails%20so%20badly%20that%20they've%20all%20fallen%20out%20and%20refuse%20to%20regrow%20normally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20far%20from%20alone.%20Lonely%2C%20atomized%2C%20burnt%20out%20America%20is%20obsessed%20with%20hobbies.%20%26quot%3BGrandma%20hobbies%26quot%3B%20are%20trending.%20Pickleball%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsfia.org%2Fresources%2Fas-pickleball-continues-unprecedented-growth-in-every-age-group-and-region-for-third-straight-year-significant-investments-still-needed-for-court-and-facility-demand%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efastest-growing%20sport%20in%20America%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Run%20clubs%20are%20the%20new%20dating%20apps.%20Chess%20is%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsexism-cheating-nightclubs-internet-inside-dark-heart-modern-chess-toxic-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20nightclub%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20no%20coincidence%20this%20is%20happening%20as%20morale%20at%20work%20is%20tanking%2C%20especially%20among%20young%20people.%20For%20the%20first%20time%20in%20almost%2020%20years%2C%20workers%20under%2035%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-employee-engagement-workplace-morale-careers-boomers-gen-x-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20disillusioned%20with%20work%20than%20those%20over%2035%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20got%20into%20trail%20running%20right%20as%20digital%20media%20was%20collapsing%3B%20the%20jobs%20I%20had%20spent%20my%20career%20dreaming%20of%20were%20ceasing%20to%20exist%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20more%20fragile%20than%20ever%20to%20tie%20my%20identity%20and%20life%20satisfaction%20to%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20us%20shape%20our%20lives%20around%20work%3A%20We%20choose%20a%20city%20based%20on%20where%20our%20industry%20is%2C%20and%20choose%20a%20home%20with%20a%20reasonable%20commute%20in%20mind.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-find-work-employment-hiring-slowdown-careers-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echaotic%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20workers%20feel%20an%20increasing%20loss%20of%20agency%2C%20some%20of%20them%2C%20myself%20included%2C%20are%20reclaiming%20it%20by%20shaping%20their%20lives%20around%20their%20hobbies%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20secret%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanalog-hobbies-antidote-to-ai-brain-rot-career-path-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehobbies%20are%20good%20for%20us%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20reduce%20stress%2C%20help%20us%20form%20social%20connections%2C%20and%20strengthen%20our%20sense%20of%20self.%20For%20extreme%20hobbyists%2C%20they%20can%20shape%20your%20entire%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Giaco%20Furino%2C%20a%2039-year-old%20board%20game%20enthusiast%20based%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20his%20hobby%20literally%20became%20work.%20He's%20an%20editor%20for%20a%20tabletop%20game%20reviews%20site%2C%20on%20top%20of%20his%20fulltime%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wake%20up%20at%20six%20and%20I'm%20taking%20photos%20of%20a%20board%20game%20for%20my%20review%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20work%20I'm%20trying%20to%20get%20people%20together%20to%20play%20a%20game%20or%20I'm%20playing%20games%20solo%20to%20get%20the%20feel%20of%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Furino%20isn't%20doing%20it%20for%20the%20money%2C%20and%20doesn't%20have%20aspirations%20to%20turn%20this%20gig%20into%20his%20full-time%20work.%20He%20took%20the%20job%20to%20codify%20his%20passion%20for%20board%20games%20into%20his%20daily%20life.%20The%20job%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bhas%20done%20exactly%20what%20I%20wanted%20it%20to%20do%2C%20which%20was%20cram%20gaming%20into%20every%20non-work%20moment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20sees%20it%2C%20free%20time%20is%20water%2C%20and%20it's%20up%20to%20us%20to%20choose%20the%20shape%20of%20the%20vessel%20we%20put%20our%20water%20in.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20make%20the%20shape%20of%20that%20vessel%20sitting%20on%20the%20couch%20watching%20TV%20for%20three%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BOr%20the%20shape%20of%20that%20vessel%20could%20be%20getting%20people%20together%20to%20play%20a%20board%20game.%20And%20one%20of%20those%20may%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20difficult%20to%20do%20%E2%80%A6%20but%20it's%20so%20much%20more%20rewarding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20common%20feeling%20among%20hardcore%20hobbyists%3A%20a%20sense%20that%20if%20you%20aren't%20vigilant%2C%20your%20free%20time%20will%20slip%20through%20your%20fingers%2C%20or%20get%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-hardcore-era-employee-changes-att-memo-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esnatched%20back%20by%20your%20employer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHumans%20didn't%20always%20think%20of%20leisure%20as%20pure%20relaxation.%20Brad%20Aeon%2C%20Ph.D.%2C%20a%20consultant%20who%20specializes%20in%20productivity%20and%20time%20management%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20in%20Ancient%20Greece%20%26quot%3Bleisure%20time%26quot%3B%20consisted%20of%20activities%20like%20public%20debate%2C%20philosophy%20and%20astronomy.%20%26quot%3BThings%20that%20were%20demanding%20mentally%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202026%2C%20we're%20almost%20certainly%20not%20at%20the%20zenith%20of%20our%20leisure%20powers.%20We%20know%20scrolling%20is%20bad%20for%20us%20and%20we%20need%20to%20take%20breaks%20from%20work%20to%20avoid%20burnout.%20But%20taking%20a%20week%20off%20and%20expecting%20leisure%20to%20come%20naturally%20sets%20us%20up%20for%20feeling%20guilty%20and%20twitchy%20%E2%80%94%20because%20we%20have%20no%20clue%20what%20to%20do%20to%20enjoy%20our%20time%20away%20from%20work%2C%20Aeon%20explains.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20spend%20your%20entire%20time%20working%2C%20that%20means%20you%20haven't%20spent%20the%20time%20to%20build%20hobbies%20and%20leisure%20time%20that%20feels%20absorbing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20we're%20so%20work-obsessed%2C%20reshaping%20your%20life%20around%20a%20hobby%20instead%20can%20feel%20counter-cultural.%20Mary%20Beth%20Yale%2C%20a%2036-year-old%20sales%20executive%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20recalls%20a%20few%20months%20into%20learning%20to%20surf%20in%20Mexico%20when%20a%20more%20experienced%20surfer%20warned%20her%2C%20%26quot%3BNow%20that%20you%20can%20surf%2C%20you%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20live%20away%20from%20the%20water.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20she%20didn't%20really%20know%20what%20he%20meant.%20But%20a%20few%20years%20later%20his%20premonition%20came%20true%3A%20Today%20Yale%20lives%20a%20half%20block%20from%20the%20beach%20in%20Venice.%20%26quot%3BI%20arranged%20my%20life%20for%20surfing%20convenience%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20a%20lifestyle%20that%20Yale%20thought%20was%20available%20to%20her%20when%20she%20was%20younger.%20%26quot%3BOur%20mom%20is%20an%20excellent%20skier%2C%20but%20never%20centered%20her%20life%20around%20skiing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Yale's%20mom%20focused%20her%20life%20around%20raising%20a%20family%20outside%20Dallas%2C%20and%20put%20her%20own%20hobbies%20on%20the%20backburner.%20Three%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20Yale%20decided%20she%20wanted%20to%20leave%20Mexico%20City%20and%20move%20to%20somewhere%20she%20could%20surf%20every%20day%2C%20her%20sister%20asked%20her%20why%20she%20needed%20to%20surf%20so%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'well%2C%20why%20can't%20I%3F'%20And%20there%20wasn't%20a%20very%20good%20counter%20argument.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20understands%20such%20intense%20dedication%20to%20a%20hobby%20over%20a%20career%2C%20and%20it%20frequently%20draws%20concern%20and%20confusion%20from%20friends%20and%20family%20members.%20Moving%20to%20Mexico%20during%20the%20pandemic%20is%20what%20gave%20Yale%20a%20new%20approach%20to%20identity%20that%20wasn't%20built%20around%20work.%20She%20didn't%20have%20to%20work%20as%20much%20because%20her%20lifestyle%20was%20cheaper.%20And%20in%20Mexico%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20do%20for%20work%3F%26quot%3B%20wasn't%20the%20first%20question%20people%20asked%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20disorienting%20at%20first.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'I%20don't%20know%20who%20I%20am%20if%20I'm%20not%20a%20marketing%20girl%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYale%20is%20still%20passionate%20about%20her%20career.%20But%20these%20days%20she%20gets%20up%20at%205%3A30%20to%20surf%2C%20walk%20her%20dog%2C%20and%20see%20her%20friends%20on%20the%20beach%2C%20all%20before%20work.%20%26quot%3BIt%20gives%20me%20this%20sense%20of%20ownership%20over%20my%20life%20that%20%E2%80%94%20regardless%20of%20what%20my%20job%20is%20or%20what's%20going%20on%20%E2%80%94%20I've%20already%20enjoyed%20myself%20and%20gotten%20to%20do%20exactly%20what%20I%20feel%20like%20I'm%20supposed%20to%20be%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20dedicated%20hobbyist%20I%20spoke%20to%20brought%20up%20this%20value%20of%20agency.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20bosses%20are%20ramping%20up%20a%20hardcore%20work%20culture%2C%20white-collar%20job%20security%20grows%20more%20precarious%2C%20and%20Slack%20messages%20are%20sent%20at%20all%20hours%20of%20the%20day%2C%20a%20hobby%20is%20a%20resistance%2C%20a%20reset%2C%20and%20maybe%20even%20a%20way%20to%20reenergize%20your%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndy%20Pearson%2C%2041%2C%20is%20a%20fellow%20runner%20who%20has%20completed%20over%20a%20dozen%20100-mile%20races.%20He's%20also%20the%20VP%20of%20creative%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fviral-canned-water-liquid-death-raised-9-million-in-series-a-funding-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELiquid%20Death%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20he%20produces%20award-winning%20creative%20campaigns%20for%20the%20%241.4-billion%20water%20brand%2C%20and%20travels%20the%20world%20speaking%20at%20conferences%20and%20industry%20events.%20In%20his%20twenties%2C%20he%20says%2C%20he%20was%20working%20for%20an%20infamously%20demanding%20agency%20and%20didn't%20take%20a%20single%20day%20off%2C%20including%20weekends%2C%20during%20his%20first%20five%20months%20on%20the%20job.%20He%20took%20up%20ultrarunning%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20equally%20extreme%20thing%20to%20my%20extreme%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20counterbalance%20helped%20Pearson%20carve%20back%20time%20in%20his%20life%20in%20a%20way%20that%20perhaps%20pickup%20basketball%20wouldn't.%20In%20a%20strange%20way%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20kind%20of%20helped%20cancel%20each%20other%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20assume%20hobby%20obsessives%20are%20addicted%20to%20self%20improvement.%20But%20hobbies%20aren't%20just%20an%20activity%20%E2%80%94%20they%20grant%20us%20entry%20into%20niche%20worlds%2C%20each%20with%20their%20own%20culture%2C%20history%2C%20science%2C%20and%20drama.%20When%20we%20take%20up%20a%20hobby%2C%20we%20can%20return%20to%20its%20world%20simply%20by%20thinking%20about%20it.%20Yale%20introduces%20me%20to%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bmind%20surfing%26quot%3B%20which%20she%20describes%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20surfing%20that%20happens%20out%20of%20the%20water.%26quot%3B%20She's%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20planning%20a%20dream%20surf%20vacation%20to%20Indonesia%2C%20and%20has%20surf%20podcasts%20she%20listens%20to%20regularly.%20%26quot%3BIt%20almost%20makes%20the%20world%204D%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Pearson%20isn't%20a%20hardcore%20fitness%20enthusiast%20for%20the%20gains.%20He%20sees%20running%20as%20a%20sandbox%20to%20play%20in.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20curiosity%2C%20and%20about%20'what%20happens%20if%20I%20try%20this%3F'%20Or%20'what%20do%20I%20see%20if%20I%20get%20over%20the%20top%20of%20this%20mountain%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20worlds%20take%20time%20to%20learn%2C%20but%20that's%20part%20of%20the%20fun.%20When%20we%20treat%20leisure%20as%20something%20that%20should%20be%20simple%20and%20easy%2C%20we%20shortchange%20ourselves%20and%20what%20we%20can%20get%20out%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20guidance%20for%20finding%20a%20worthwhile%20hobby%20is%20to%20identify%20an%20activity%20with%20lore%2C%20history%2C%20and%20key%20players%20to%20follow.%20You%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20fall%20down%20the%20rabbit%20hole%2C%20whether%20through%20books%2C%20message%20boards%2C%20podcasts%2C%20or%20Instagram%20follows%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20a%20kickball%20league%20likely%20doesn't%20offer%2C%20but%20flyfishing%20probably%20does.%20Second%2C%20you%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20measure%20your%20progress%20at%20whatever%20hobby%20you%20choose.%20There%20is%20so%20much%20joy%20and%20excitement%20in%20being%20a%20novice%20and%20improving%20quickly%2C%20and%20then%20later%20on%20so%20much%20satisfaction%20with%20smaller%2C%20subtler%20growth.%20Third%2C%20my%20personal%20preference%20is%20to%20choose%20a%20hobby%20that%20requires%20a%20little%20gear%20but%20not%20too%20much.%20Learning%20about%20which%20yarn%20and%20needles%20you%20like%20to%20knit%20on%2C%20or%20which%20trail%20running%20shoes%20make%20you%20feel%20light%20on%20your%20feet%20is%20all%20part%20of%20the%20fun%2C%20and%20spending%20money%20on%20a%20hobby%20feels%20wholesome%20in%20a%20way%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fulta-earnings-customers-buying-beauty-products-escape-stress-makeup-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eretail%20therapy%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20I'm%20now%20fully%20on%20the%20hobby%20train%2C%20%26quot%3Bhobby%26quot%3B%20still%20feels%20diminutive%20for%20how%20seriously%20I%20take%20trail%20running.%20But%20as%20someone%20who%20excels%20at%20ruining%20the%20things%20she%20loves%20by%20being%20overly%20competitive%20about%20them%2C%20I%20like%20that%20the%20word%20reminds%20me%20of%20the%20role%20I%20want%20running%20to%20play%20in%20my%20life.%20I%20don't%20want%20running%20to%20become%20my%20job.%20Calling%20it%20my%20%26quot%3Bhobby%26quot%3B%20helps%20me%20safeguard%20my%20fun%2C%20without%20discouraging%20myself%20from%20giving%20it%20my%20very%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20surprisingly%2C%20going%20all-in%20on%20trail%20running%20is%20what%20helped%20me%20embrace%20and%20level%20up%20my%20career.%20Once%20I%20was%20no%20longer%20spending%20all%20my%20free%20time%20lusting%20after%20a%20specific%20version%20of%20a%20writing%20career%2C%20I%20looked%20around%20and%20realized%20my%20job%20as%20a%20creative%20director%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fad-industry-embraces-human-creativity-ai-era-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eadvertising%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20%E2%80%A6%20pretty%20fun!%20Inspired%20by%20the%20curiosity%20and%20whimsy%20with%20which%20I%20approached%20trail%20running%2C%20I%20started%20to%20take%20the%20same%20approach%20with%20advertising%20and%20video%20production%20%E2%80%94%20treating%20it%20as%20a%20niche%20world%20to%20explore%20versus%20a%20test%20to%20pass.%20I%20decided%20to%20become%20a%20manager%2C%20started%20reading%20the%20trades%20more%20closely%2C%20and%20took%20time%20to%20seek%20out%20creative%20inspiration%20and%20share%20it%20with%20my%20coworkers.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20running%20put%20healthy%20boundaries%20on%20my%20work%20and%20the%20role%20it%20plays%20in%20my%20self-esteem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20year%2C%20I've%20even%20returned%20to%20my%20old%20hobby%20I%20once%20swore%20off%3A%20knitting.%20I've%20acquired%20an%20ever-expanding%20bag%20of%20knitting%20supplies%2C%20and%20sometimes%20I%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20pulling%20myself%20away%20from%20my%20knitting%20to%20go%20out%20for%20a%20run.%20I%20used%20to%20be%20someone%20who%20didn't%20know%20who%20they'd%20be%20without%20work.%20Now%20I'm%20amassing%20so%20many%20hobbies%20that%20work%20is%20simply%20what%20I%20do%20when%20I'm%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20doing%20my%20hobbies.%20My%20hobbies%20have%20taught%20me%20that%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%20really%20good%20at%20retiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fcatherine-leclair%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECatherine%20LeClair%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20writer%2C%20runner%20and%20creative%20director%20living%20in%20California.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrailrunning-hobby-saved-career-identity-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1768122421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69614e57832e0ef1ead781c9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrailrunning-hobby-saved-career-identity-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20best%20way%20to%20save%20your%20career%20from%20the%20white-collar%20apocalypse%3A%20Get%20a%20hobby.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cleclair%40businessinsider.com%20(Catherine%20LeClair)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A39%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrailrunning-hobby-saved-career-identity-2026-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vijay%20To%20Appear%20Before%20Probe%20Agency%20On%20January%2012%20In%20Karur%20Stampede%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Tamilaga%20Vettri%20Kazhagam%20president%20Vijay%20is%20set%20to%20appear%20before%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Monday%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20probe%20into%