cifically%2C%26quot%3B%20I'd%20laugh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20explained%20to%20the%20kids%20that%20I%20needed%20some%20alone%20time%3B%20I%20needed%20to%20take%20a%20break.%20They%2C%20who%20are%208%2C%205%2C%20and%203%2C%20were%20relatively%20unfazed.%20My%20middle%2C%20big-feeling%20daughter%20made%20me%20promise%20to%20call%20her%20every%20two%20minutes.%20I%20wanted%20them%20to%20know%20that%20it%20was%20OK%20for%20Mom%20(or%20Dad)%20to%20step%20away%20and%20be%20alone.%20It%20didn't%20mean%20I%20loved%20them%20any%20less.%20Something%2C%20something%20about%20distance%20making%20the%20heart%20grow%20fonder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2206bb367f-da3c-44dc-a2bd-783510cc3a58%5C%22%3ESelf-care%20is%20crucial%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMental%20health%20experts%20agree.%20Solitude%20can%20be%20a%20crucial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fself-care%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eform%20of%20self-care%3C%2Fa%3E%20(unless%20it%20makes%20you%20%3Cem%3Etruly%3C%2Fem%3E%20uncomfortable%20to%20be%20totally%20alone).%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20seek%20out%20intentional%20solitude%2C%20and%20the%20demands%20on%20your%20attention%20and%20focus%20melt%20away%2C%20it%20allows%20you%20to%20have%20a%20level%20of%20awareness%20that%20can%20support%20healing%20and%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.resetoutdoors.com%2Fabout-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEmily%20Moriarty%2C%20M.Ed.%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20licensed%20professional%20counselor%20and%20director%20of%20clinical%20services%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.resetoutdoors.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReset%20Outdoors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20they%20were%20off.%20And%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20myself.%20Everything%20was%20weirdly%20quiet.%20Clean.%20Empty.%20I%20loved%20it.%20I%20had%20a%20couple%20of%20low-key%20plans%20over%20the%20next%20few%20days%2C%20but%20my%20goal%20was%20to%20savor%20the%20silence%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Living%20room%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696159d0832e0ef1ead783a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20really%20enjoyed%20her%20time%20alone.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%205%20p.m.%20rolled%20around%20on%20the%20first%20night%2C%20I%20started%20making%20dinner%20while%20listening%20to%20music.%20I%20danced%20a%20little.%20I%20ate%20while%20reading%20a%20book.%20No%20one%20argued%20with%20me%20that%20they%20didn't%20like%20what%20was%20served.%20Cleanup%20was%20easy.%20I%20put%20my%20dishes%20away.%20I%20didn't%20need%20to%20sweep%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3EI%20%3C%2Fem%3Edon't%20spill%20things%20on%20the%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20turned%20my%20phone%20off%3B%20I%20didn't%20need%20an%20alarm.%20No%20one%20needed%20to%20reach%20me%2C%20and%20if%20they%20did%2C%20they%20could%20wait.%20Dad%20was%20more%20than%20capable.%20I%20slept%20in.%20I%20drank%20coffee%20on%20the%20couch%20in%20front%20of%20the%20fire%20in%20my%20pajamas.%20I%20forced%20myself%20to%20allow%20things%20to%20move%20slowly%20%E2%80%94%20something%20I%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20doing%20with%20or%20without%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSolitude%20doesn't%20include%20sitting%20alone%20in%20an%20office%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20Moriarty%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20to%20be%20non-work%2C%20non-caregiving%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20was%20time%20for%20the%20Big%20Holiday%20Meal%2C%20I%20thought%20I'd%20feel%20a%20little%20lonely.%20But%20I%20didn't%2C%20and%20that%2C%20I%20realized%2C%20was%20because%20this%20was%20my%20%3Cem%3Echoice%3C%2Fem%3E.%20I%20knew%20my%20family%20was%20enjoying%20themselves%20with%20relatives%20they%20don't%20often%20see%20and%20having%20a%20little%20vacation.%20And%20I%20knew%20that%20they'd%20all%20be%20home%20before%20I%20knew%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f4022e7b-6e04-407d-8b09-edbc544eb55f%5C%22%3EI%20had%20a%20little%20mom%20guilt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20fourth%20day%2C%20the%20air%20was%20thick%20with%20anticipation%20of%20the%20kids%20and%20Jeff%20coming%20home.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20couldn't%20watch%20TV%20fast%20enough.%20I%20couldn't%20sit%20in%20a%20quiet%2C%20empty%20house%20fast%20enough.%20I%20couldn't%20drink%20enough%20coffee%20fast%20enough.%20But%20when%20I%20started%20making%20dinner%20at%205%20p.m.%2C%20awaiting%20their%208%20p.m.%20arrival%2C%20I%20realized%20if%20I%20had%20to%20keep%20doing%20this%2C%20I%20might%20get%20a%20little%E2%80%A6%20bored%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20sure%20that%20has%20more%20to%20do%20with%20the%20stark%20contrast%20of%20raising%20three%20kids%2C%20co-running%20a%20household%2C%20and%20having%20a%20(fairly%20successful)%20career%2C%20and%20four%20days%20of%20abrupt%2C%20near-total%20solitude.%20If%20I%20didn't%20have%20kids%20at%20all%2C%20I'm%20sure%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20bored%20at%207%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20have%20since%20asked%20me%20if%20this%20will%20be%20my%20new%20holiday%20tradition.%20I%20did%20like%20it%2C%20maybe%20a%20bit%20too%20much%2C%20but%20it%20feels%20wrong%20to%20indefinitely%20celebrate%20the%20holidays%20without%20my%20kith%20and%20kin.%20Four%20days%20weren't%20enough%20to%20assuage%20Mom%20Guilt%2C%20apparently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-spent-the-holidays-alone-as-a-mom-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1768085221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696153cd04eda4732f2ecffc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-spent-the-holidays-alone-as-a-mom-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20sent%20my%20husband%20